<collectingCountry box="[1147,1305,607,632]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="37" pageNumber="521">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, were originally described as distinct species, but D. Nagorsen and J. R. Tamsitt in 1981 found morphological variation to be continuous from Central America into 
<collectingCountry box="[723,790,800,829]" name="Peru" pageId="37" pageNumber="521">Peru</collectingCountry>
, so are considered as synonymshere. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
